sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J56017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: sequence containing necessary DNA for controlled chemotaxis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: DNA includes switching mechanisms and componenents necssary for directed motility towards aspartate or phenylalanine (does not include wild-type CheW, which may be inserted between restriction sites on opposite side of inversion sequence). Sequence must be placed in strain with all receptors knocked out (tar, tsr, tap, trg, ser) as well as CheW. Switching mechanism is irreversibly activated by arabinose. Strain switches from phenylalanine chemotaxis to aspartate chemotaxis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Matt Eames
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: CheW* (VM108), Tar receptor codon-optimized to avoid recombination.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J56010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Component to be used in nucleotide sequence inversion. Addition of arabinose activates switching mechanism. Switch is irreversible.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Matt Eames

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J56012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Invertible sequence of dna includes Ptrc promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Seuqence is inverted by the FimE protein. Inside recognition sequence is a Ptrc promoter sequence. Switch is irreversible.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Matt Eames

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J56013

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Matt Eames

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J56001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CheW with VM108 mutation for orthogonal interaction with Tar EA400
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Part contains CheW with valine to methionine mutation at position 108 to facilitate an orthogonal interaction with a Tar chemotaxis receptor with a EA400 mutation. CheW VM108 will have only limited interaction with wild-type Tar.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Matt Eames
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: CheW was cloned out of the genome and mutated on plasmid

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J56002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Tar EA400 has orthogonal interaction with CheW VM108
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Tar (aspartate-sensitive chemotaxis receptor) mutated (EA400) to have orthogonal interaction with CheW VM108. Has minimal interaction with wild-type CheW.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Matt Eames
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Mutation was originally evolved in Tsr (EA402), this residue occurs in position 400 after sequence alignment.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Tar mutated to respond to phenylalanine instead of aspartate
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Tar (aspartate-sensitive chemotaxis receptor) with mutations to respond to phenylalanine. Protein has minimal response to aspartate.
